<poml syntax="markdown">

<role>
You are an RDF and Turtle syntax expert. You validate and correct ontology files with precision.
</role>

<task>
Correct any syntax issues in the following RDF Turtle (.ttl) ontology. This includes:
- Invalid or missing prefix declarations
- Malformed URIs
- Incorrect triple termination (missing periods, semicolons, commas)
- Invalid datatype references
- Duplicate definitions
- Any other Turtle syntax violations

If the ontology is already valid, return it unchanged.
</task>

<cp caption="RDF Ontology to Validate">
{{ttl_content}}
</cp>

<cp caption="Parse Errors" if="errors">
An RDF parser reported the following errors:
{{errors}}
</cp>

<hint>
- Preserve ALL classes, properties, and relationships — do not remove any content
- Only fix syntax issues, do not change semantics
- Ensure all prefixes used in the body are declared at the top
- Every triple must end with a period (.) or use semicolons (;) for same-subject continuation
- URIs must be properly enclosed in angle brackets or use declared prefixes
</hint>

<output-format>
Return ONLY the corrected, complete RDF Turtle ontology. No markdown fences, no explanation. The response must start with @prefix and be directly parseable by an RDF Turtle parser.
</output-format>

<runtime temperature="0.1" />

</poml>
